Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf=20wave=2020=20W20B=20patch=200090=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20engine-tick=20decomposition=20(Lever=20A=20finer)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DOS-PORT (patch 0090, Phase 9 wave 20 W20B). Decomposes the engine_tick
budget (17.8 ms audio-off / 21.1 ms audio-on per W20A2 + W20A
measurements) into 4 named sub-buckets + 1 residual derived stat.

Scope reduction: original W20B plan was flip()-body brackets
(yield_call / flush_renderer_call / dirty_rects_clear /
maybe_flush_audits) + engine_tick brackets. After W20C probe results
(YIELD.EXE 0.515 µs flat, CFFSYNC.EXE explained the LOG-line tail
cost, IRQRATE.EXE confirmed timer/keyboard IRQs ~18 Hz are
negligible), all 4 flip()-body brackets dropped — they would have
measured sub-ms work that doesn't compose to meaningful fps gains.
The flip()-body draft (263+/1-) parked to
tests/probes/wip-w20b-flip-body-brackets.diff (gitignored) for
salvage if 50 fps stretch work surfaces a need for that decomposition.

The engine_tick decomposition stays load-bearing because:
  - The 17.8 ms audio-off engine_tick is where remaining audio-
    independent time lives. Lever G (audio rate reduction) doesn't
    address it; needs separate analysis.
  - The 3.3 ms delta between audio-off and audio-on engine_tick is
    audio-IRQ-in-Game::tick wall-clock cost. Useful cross-check
    against Lever G's predicted savings.
  - 50 fps stretch goal needs to identify which sub-bucket is the
    largest fixed cost; this decomposition tells us.

Implementation:

1. **`SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FINE_INSTR=1`** env helper (strict-1, default
   OFF). Cached static-const-bool — -O2 hoists per-tick guards.
   Originally introduced for the parked flip-body brackets; reused
   here.

2. **4 RAII timer structs** in
   `vendor/nxengine-evo/src/Utils/diagnostic_timers.h`, mirroring
   the existing `EngineTickTimer` pattern from patch 0062:
   - `ClearScreenTimer` — wraps `Renderer::clearScreen(BLACK)` at
     game.cpp:228.
   - `TscInterpTimer` — wraps `tsc->RunScripts()` at game.cpp:238
     (only fires on `!game.paused` branch; n=actual_count).
   - `ModeTickTimer` — wraps `tickfunctions[].OnTick()` at game.cpp
     line 233 (paused branch) AND line 247 (normal branch); one or
     other always fires; n=100/100. THIS IS THE BIG ONE — captures
     sprite update + AI + drawcall exec + room logic.
   - `DebugOverlayTimer` — wraps `DrawDebug() + console.Draw()`
     lumped at lines 250-251.

   Each timer's destructor: read elapsed ns, write to per-tick dt
   local (file-scope, used for residual computation), bounds-check
   sample-array idx, push if room. All gated on
   `engine_tick_fine_instr_active()` (free-function wrapper around
   the anonymous-namespace `_abl_fine_instr()` helper).

3. **Storage** (file-scope in Renderer.cpp's `NXE::Diag` namespace):
   - 4 sample arrays + 4 idx counters (mirrors the W20A
     `_flip_phase_samples_*` pattern at the engine-tick layer).
   - 4 per-tick dt locals (reset at Game::tick entry; written by
     each timer's destructor; consumed by residual computation).
   - 1 residual sample array + idx.

4. **Residual derived stat** computed at end of `Game::tick`:
   ```
   _residual = engine_tick_total_dt
             - clear_screen_dt - tsc_interp_dt
             - mode_tick_dt - debug_overlay_dt
   ```
   Signed math + clamp at 0. Reflects un-bracketed time inside
   `Game::tick` body — `debug_clear`, the esc-pause check, branch
   overhead, and any uncaught small calls. Self-validating: small
   residual (<1 ms median) means brackets are exhaustive; large
   residual means there's still an unbracketed chunk worth
   investigating.

5. **Audit-flush emission** in
   `_maybe_flush_phase_timing_audit()`: 5 new
   `[engine-tick-stat n=N phase=<NAME> min=X.XX med=Y.YY mean=Z.ZZ
   p95=P.PP max=M.MM ms]` lines per 100-tick block when
   FINE_INSTR=1. Distinct prefix `engine-tick-stat` (vs W20A's
   `flip-stat` and parked W20B-flip-body's `flip-fine-stat`) so
   grep tooling separates the three layers without ambiguity.
   Empty-block placeholder lines emitted when n=0 (e.g.
   tsc_interp on paused-only blocks) so per-block log shape is
   uniform.

6. **Same `_compute_flip_phase_stats` helper** reused (W20A's
   sort/min/med/mean/p95/max/2-decimal infrastructure is
   layer-agnostic).

Skipped per flush-instr's earlier guidance:
- `audio_mix_stage` separate bracket: SoundManager / Mix_HookMusic
  fires off-thread (audio IRQ context); no clean call site in
  Game::tick body. The audio-IRQ wall-clock cost shows up in the
  delta between audio-on and audio-off engine_tick_total which W20A
  + W20A2 already measure.
- `drawcall_exec` separate from `mode_tick`: drawcalls happen
  INSIDE per-mode `OnTick` handlers in modes/*.cpp; bracketing
  them separately would require touching 10+ files. Per
  flush-instr: collapse to mode_tick; let the residual catch
  sub-decomposition for later if needed.
- Fifth `debug_clear` bracket: tiny call (probably ns); leave in
  residual to keep output bracket count at 4.

Cross-namespace plumbing: `_abl_fine_instr()` is in
`NXE::Graphics::(anonymous namespace)` (TU-local internal linkage).
The RAII timer destructors in `diagnostic_timers.h` need to gate on
the env. Solution: forward-declared free function
`NXE::Diag::engine_tick_fine_instr_active()` at namespace scope, with
a 1-line wrapper definition in Renderer.cpp after the anonymous
namespace closes that calls `::NXE::Graphics::_abl_fine_instr()`.
Anonymous-namespace symbols are accessible by their parent-namespace
qualified name within the same TU per ISO C++.

Hot-path cost when FINE_INSTR unset:
- 4 RAII destructors per tick (each reads SDL_GetTicksNS at
  construction unconditionally; gating happens at destruction).
- Construction overhead: 4 SDL_GetTicksNS reads per tick
  (~unavoidable; mirrors EngineTickTimer's existing pattern).
- ~5 KB unused static state.
- Residual computation: gated on engine_tick_fine_instr_active(),
  so 0 cost when env unset.

If construction-time SDL_GetTicksNS ever shows up as overhead in
real-HW data, gate the constructors too (constructor only sets t0
if active). Not done in this patch — keeps consistency with the
existing EngineTickTimer pattern; can be optimized later.

Test plan (subsequent task #3 / #4 / #5 equivalents for W20B iter):
- DOSBox-X smoke (build-qa): 3 configs.
  - A: env-unset baseline (no [flip-stat], no [engine-tick-stat]).
  - B: SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR=1 alone (W20A coarse only;
       no engine-tick-stat lines).
  - C: SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FLIP_INSTR=1 + SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FINE_INSTR=1
       (W20A coarse + W20B engine-tick decomp; both layers emit).
- Real-HW iter (realhw): single PLAY at config C; W20B LOG_TAG.
- Analysis (flush-instr): identify which sub-bucket dominates the
  17.8 ms audio-off engine_tick. Guides 50 fps stretch lever
  selection.

Documentation: docs/BOOT.md FINE_INSTR entry already exists from
patch 0090's flip-body draft (now archived); engine-tick reuses
the same env var so docs entry stays as-is. May need editorial
pass to rewrite the FINE_INSTR description for engine-tick semantics
but the env var name is unchanged.

